import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['normal'] = pd.to_numeric(data['normal'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='normal', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].mean(), color='red', label='mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['normal'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].median(), color='green', label='median: {:.2f}'.format(data['normal'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of normal temperature?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['actual'] = pd.to_datetime(data['actual'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='actual', y='forecast', data=data)
    chart.set(title='How does the actual temperature compare to the forecasted temperature?')
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['actual'] = pd.to_datetime(data['actual'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['difference'] = data['actual'] - data['forecast']
    data['difference'] = data['difference'].dt.days
    sns.boxplot(x=data['difference'], color='lightblue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['difference'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['difference'].mean()))
    plt.title('What is the average difference between the actual and forecasted temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='day')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='day', y='normal', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['normal'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['normal'].median()))
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the trend of temperature over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
